code: import pandas as pd import numpy as np from pathlib import Path from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split import lightgbm as lgb from scipy.stats import skew, kurtosis from sklearn.metrics import mean_absolute_error input_path = Path("./input") train_labels = pd.read_csv(input_path / "train.csv") def extract_features(file_path): df = pd.read_csv(file_path) features = {} for col in df.columns: col_data = df[col] # Handle NaN values if col_data.isna().all(): col_data_filled = col_data.fillna(0) else: col_data_filled = col_data.fillna(col_data.mean()) # Basic stats features[f"{col}_mean"] = col_data_filled.mean() features[f"{col}_std"] = col_data_filled.std() features[f"{col}_max"] = col_data_filled.max() features[f"{col}_min"] = col_data_filled.min() features[f"{col}_q95"] = col_data_filled.quantile(0.95) features[f"{col}_q05"] = col_data_filled.quantile(0.05) # Distribution stats features[f"{col}_skew"] = skew(col_data_filled) features[f"{col}_kurtosis"] = kurtosis(col_data_filled) # Autocorrelation autocorr_lag1 = col_data_filled.autocorr(lag=1) autocorr_lag100 = col_data_filled.autocorr(lag=100) features[f"{col}_ac_lag1"] = autocorr_lag1 if not np.isnan(autocorr_lag1) else 0 features[f"{col}_ac_lag100"] = ( autocorr_lag100 if not np.isnan(autocorr_lag100) else 0 ) # Rolling window stats window_size = 1000 rolling_mean = col_data_filled.rolling(window_size).mean().dropna() rolling_std = col_data_filled.rolling(window_size).std().dropna() if len(rolling_mean) > 0: features[f"{col}_roll_mean_mean"] = rolling_mean.mean() features[f"{col}_roll_mean_std"] = rolling_mean.std() features[f"{col}_roll_std_mean"] = rolling_std.mean() features[f"{col}_roll_std_std"] = rolling_std.std() else: features.update( { f"{col}_roll_{stat}": 0 for stat in ["mean_mean", "mean_std", "std_mean", "std_std"] } ) # FFT features fft = np.fft.rfft(col_data_filled.values) magnitude = np.abs(fft)[1:] if len(magnitude) > 0: features[f"{col}_fft_mean"] = magnitude.mean() features[f"{col}_fft_std"] = magnitude.std() features[f"{col}_fft_max"] = magnitude.max() features[f"{col}_fft_min"] = magnitude.min() features[f"{col}_fft_q95"] = np.quantile(magnitude, 0.95) features[f"{col}_fft_q05"] = np.quantile(magnitude, 0.05) else: features.update( { f"{col}_fft_{stat}": 0 for stat in ["mean", "std", "max", "min", "q95", "q05"] } ) return pd.Series(features) # Process training data print("Processing training files...") train_features = [] for seg_id in train_labels["segment_id"]: features = extract_features(input_path / f"train/{seg_id}.csv") train_features.append(features) train_features = pd.concat(train_features, axis=1).T.reset_index(drop=True) train_data = pd.concat([train_labels, train_features], axis=1) # Split validation X_train, X_val, y_train, y_val = train_test_split( train_data.drop(["segment_id", "time_to_eruption"], axis=1), train_data["time_to_eruption"], test_size=0.2, random_state=42, ) # Optimized model parameters model = lgb.LGBMRegressor( num_leaves=255, learning_rate=0.005, n_estimators=5000, max_depth=-1, reg_alpha=0.2, reg_lambda=0.3, min_child_samples=20, random_state=42, n_jobs=-1, verbose=1, ) model.fit( X_train, y_train, eval_set=[(X_val, y_val)], callbacks=[lgb.early_stopping(stopping_rounds=200), lgb.log_evaluation(100)], ) # Validate val_pred = model.predict(X_val) mae = mean_absolute_error(y_val, val_pred) print(f"Validation MAE: {mae:.4f}") # Process test data print("\nProcessing test files...") test_files = list((input_path / "test").glob("*.csv")) submission = [] for test_file in test_files: seg_id = test_file.stem features = extract_features(test_file) features_df = pd.DataFrame([features]) pred = model.predict(features_df)[0] submission.append({"segment_id": seg_id, "time_to_eruption": pred}) # Save submission submission_df = pd.DataFrame(submission) submission_df.to_csv("./submission/submission.csv", index=False) print("Submission saved!")
